Subnetting

IPv4  -> Limited

1) use Private IP  - 10.0.0.0 , 172.16.x.x, 192.0.0.0

2) use IPv6

3) use Subnetting



Subnetting
    network within a network
            or
    Logically Division of IP Address



    190.20.10.2
    10 computers  ----router-------router-------  20 computers
                        |             |
                        |             |
                       50 computer    4 computer
                        190.20.10.15 can not of other network
                        15.10.0.1

   190.20.0.0 network id

   each router interface should different network id

   Router is inter-networking device  used to communicate  b/w two different networks
   within network communication use switch



Benefits of Subnetting

   10.0.0.0                                         200.10.10.0
    10 computers  ----router-------router-------  20 computers
                        |             |
                        |             |
                       50 computer    4 computer
                       130.10.0.0        200.10.11.0


     10.0.0.0    ->  10.0.0.1   10.0.0.2   10.0.0.3  10.0.0.4   10.0.0.5   10.0.0.6   10.0.0.7  10.0.0.8   10.0.0.9   10.0.0.10 = total = 2^24 -2

     130.10.0.0 -> 130.10.0.0 --130.10.0.1 ...130.10.0.2......................130.10.0.50  = total = 2^16 -2 = 65534

     200.10.10.0  ->  200.10.10.0  ........200.10.10.20 = total = 2^8 -2 = 254



     By default CIDR value of class A - /8
                              class B - /16
                              class C - /24


     If by default it's mention means no subnetting , other value subnetting has happened

     10.0.0.0/8
     130.10.0.0/16
     200.10.10.0/24


